tests.sic.rnqt.norm

Class RnQTCnormHeurOpt

  • java.lang.Object
    • tests.sic.rnqt.norm.RnQTCnormHeurOpt
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    OptimizerIntf

    public class RnQTCnormHeurOpt
extends java.lang.Object
implements OptimizerIntf
    class implements an approximate heuristic optimizer over ALL three variables of the (R,nQ,T) policy, namely the reorder point R, the batch size Q and the review period T as described in Christou, Skouri and Lagodimos (2020): "Fast evaluation of a periodic review inventory policy", Computers and Industrial Engineering, 144. The system being optimized faces stochastic demands as described in the class RnQTCnorm.

    Title: popt4jlib

    Description: A Parallel Meta-Heuristic Optimization Library in Java

    1.0

      • snQTCnormApprox2

        private double snQTCnormApprox2(double s,
                                double Q,
                                double T)
        computes the approximate cost function arising from the Po approximation by the formula Komin(1, μT/Q). Note that for this function to work, the _norm data field must have been correctly set prior to calling the method.
        Parameters:
        s - double reorder point
        Q - double batch size must be positive
        T - double review period must be ≥ (3.5σ/μ)2
        Returns:
        double the approximation value

      • main

        public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
        test-driver method to test the class functionality. Invoke as: java -cp <classpath> tests.sic.rnqt.norm.RnQTCnormHeurOpt <Kr> <Ko> <L> <μ> <σ> <h> <p> [epsT(0.01)] [epsQ(0.1)] [epsR(1.e-4)] [dbglvl(0)] . It prints out the heuristic set of best (R,Q,T) parameters it could find plus the associated cost, and the elapsed time.
